## Installation

### For Users

**Coming Soon:**

- App Store (iOS)
- Google Play (Android)

### For Developers

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/zeropoint-privacy-app.git

# Navigate to project
cd zeropoint-privacy-app

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start development server
npx expo start
```

**Requirements:**

- Node.js 18+
- npm or yarn
- Expo CLI (installed automatically)

**Run on device:**

```bash
# iOS Simulator
npx expo start --ios

# Android Emulator
npx expo start --android

# Physical device via Expo Go
npx expo start
# Scan QR code with Expo Go app
```

-----

## Architecture

- **Framework:** React Native (Expo)
- **State Management:** React Hooks
- **Storage:** AsyncStorage (encrypted on-device only)
- **Network:** None. Zero network calls.
- **Analytics:** None.
- **Third-party SDKs:** None.

-----

## Privacy Architecture

All data stays on your device. Always.

**What ZEROPOINT stores:**

1. A snapshot of your permission states (encrypted locally) â€” so it can restore them
1. An audit log of the last 25 toggle events (encrypted locally) â€” deletable by you

**What ZEROPOINT NEVER does:**

- Send data to servers (there are no servers)
- Create accounts (there is no account system)
- Track usage (there is no analytics)
- Collect personal information (impossible by design)

Even if compelled, there is nothing to hand over because nothing exists anywhere except on your device, encrypted, under your control.

-----

